Underneath the ancient trees,
Where the moss grows soft and deep,
Whispers of the forest spirits
Cradle all our dreams to sleep.

In this sacred, timeless silence,
In the arms of earth so kind,
We discover natureâ€™s magic,
In the wonders left behind.

